SIMPLE: interface
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: interface
<hw>interface</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a surface forming a
common boundary between two things, especially between two fluids.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>hardware that links one
device with another (especially a computer).</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>That part of a computer
program which controls the way a program interacts with a user; the
manner of inputting and outputting of data, and the way information is
presented on a computer monitor; also called <altname>user
interface</altname>; <as>as, a graphical user <ex>interface</ex>; a
character-based <ex>interface</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interfacial</ent>⟦br⟧
